  "text": "Moving away from small , we expect the Z branching ratio to increase, as the contributions from dimension 6 operators to bino decay are roughly equal for the higgs and Z modes. This is shown in Fig. 9 . The effects of interference between the dimension 5 and dimension 6 operators on the higgs amplitude also grow more pronounced for larger . For > 0, the interference is destructive for tan γ ∈ (1/ tan 2 β, 1), and vice versa for < 0. [CITATION_1] For extremely large , the approximations based on being in the higgsino decoupling limit break down as m λ /µ approaches O(1). Ultimately, the higgs mode is kinematically excluded once the mass of the lightest neutralino (by now predominantly higgsino) drops below the higgs mass.",
